      "verified_method": "source",
      "verified_notes": "Write Interception section rewritten to honestly disclose the full stack: tool-layer interception is default; nono process sandbox (Landlock on Linux, Seatbelt on macOS via kernel/sandbox.rs) blocks escape writes at OS layer; optional FUSE passthrough (fuse/passthrough.rs, built with --features fuse, invoked via ostk mount) mirrors the tree for full write observability. Previous version claimed No FUSE/LD_PRELOAD/ptrace as absolutes, which was wrong — FUSE IS an optional feature."
    },
